{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Demetrio Carceller Coll | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | restingplace = | nationality = Portuguese | residence = London, England | education = | alma mater = | occupation = founder, chairman and president of MV Holding | title = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | known for = owner of [[Disa Corp]] and [[S.A. Damm|Damm]] | boards = | salary = | networth = US$2.1 billion (April 2017) | spouse = married | children = 4, including [[Demetrio Carceller Arce]] | parents = [[Demetrio Carceller Segura]] | relations = | website = }}
'''Demetrio Carceller Coll''' is a Portuguese [[billionaire]] heir and businessman.
Carceller Coll inherited two companies from his father, [[Demetrio Carceller Segura]], the petrol station chain [[Disa Corp]], and the Spanish brewery [[S.A. Damm|Damm]].<ref name="forbes1">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/demetrio-carceller-coll/ |title=Demetrio Carceller Coll |publisher=Forbes.com |date=1 January 1970 |accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref> He is a part owner in the Spanish food company [[Ebro Foods]] and the property company [[Sacyr]].<ref name="forbes1"/>
Carceller Coll is married, with four children, and lives in London and Portugal.<ref name="forbes1"/> His businesses are now run by his son, [[Demetrio Carceller Arce]].<ref name="forbes1"/>
