{{Infobox person | name = Kirill Minovalov | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Кирилл Вадимович Миновалов | birth_date = {{birth-date and age|April 22, 1971}} | birth_place = [[Moscow]], [[USSR]] | residence = Moscow | citizenship = [[Russia]] | education = [[Moscow Institute for Railway Engineering]] | occupation = | known_for = founder of [[Avangard Bank]] and [[Avangard Malz]] | networth = | children = | website = }}
'''Kirill Vadimovich Minovalov''' ({{lang-ru|Кирилл Вадимович Миновалов}}, also ''Cyril Minovalov''; born April 22, 1971) is a [[Russia]]n businessman.
==Biography== Kirill Minovalov graduated in Systems Engineering from [[Moscow Institute for Railway Engineering]] in 1993.<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/finance/stocks/officerProfile?symbol=AVAN.MM&officerId=1299318 Minovalov, Kirill] // [[Reuters.com]]</ref> He was quick to take advantage of [[Economic history of the Russian Federation#Transition to Market Economy|Russia’s economic reforms in the early 1990s]].<ref>Vladimir Karnozov. [http://www.ainonline.com/aviation-news/aviation-international-news/2009-10-28/pilot-suspects-static-electricity-citation-x-pitot-failures Pilot suspects static electricity in Citation X pitot failures] // Ain Online, October 28, 2009</ref> In 1994, he founded the bank "{{Interlanguage link multi|Avangard Bank|ru|3=Авангард (банк)|lt=Avangard|vertical-align=sup}}" and still serves as its president and core shareholder.<ref>[https://globenewswire.com/news-release/2013/10/21/581904/10053453/en/Russia-Magazine-Major-Russian-Online-Bank-Set-to-Go-Public-Stirring-Talks-About-New-Financial-Bubble.html Major Russian Online Bank Set to Go Public Stirring Talks About New Financial Bubble] // [[Russia! magazine]], October 21, 2013</ref> Then he became engaged in the malting business, building the largest malting company in [[Germany]]. In 2006, he bought the assets of the bankrupt company {{Interlanguage link multi|Friedrich Weissheimer Malzfabrik|de|3=Friedrich Weissheimer Malzfabrik|lt=Weissheimer Malz|vertical-align=sup}} and created [[Avangard Malz]] which has the capacity of more than 340000 mt of malt per year. According to ''[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]]'', Minovalov is the [[List of Russian people by net worth|132nd richest person in Russia]].<ref name="Forbes">{{cite web | title = 200 БОГАТЕЙШИХ БИЗНЕСМЕНОВ РОССИИ / КИРИЛЛ МИНОВАЛОВ| url =http://www.forbes.ru/profile/kirill-minovalov | publisher = [[Forbes]] | language = ru}}</ref>
On September 19, 2011, [[luxury vehicle]]s knocked down and killed four Moldovan workers on the road to [[Domodedovo International Airport]]. According to activists of the [[Society of Blue Buckets|Blue Buckets movement]], Kirill Minovalov was a passenger in the cortege.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://echo.msk.ru/blog/danilalindele/813298-echo/ |title= Под колесами VIP-кортежа погибли 4 человека |last= Линдэле |first= Данила |date= 20 September 2011 |publisher= [[Echo of Moscow]] |language= ru |archive-url= |archive-date= |dead-url= |accessdate= 2017-07-24 |quote= |ref= |postscript= |subscription= |registration=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://echo.msk.ru/blog/danilalindele/813759-echo/ |title= Чей кортеж сбил четырех человек у Домодедово?|last= Линдэле |first= Данила |date= 21 September 2011 |publisher= [[Echo of Moscow]] |language= ru |archive-url= |archive-date= |dead-url= |accessdate= 2017-07-24 |quote= |ref= |postscript= |subscription= |registration=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://themoscowtimes.com/news/bank-linked-to-fatal-car-crash-9714 |title= Bank Linked to Fatal Car Crash |date= September 22, 2011 |year= |publisher= [[The Moscow Times]] |location= |archive-url= |archive-date= |dead-url= |accessdate= 2017-07-24}}</ref>
